author: Kaitlan Collins
title: Will Caitlyn Jenner Dance With Donald Trump At The Inauguration? Jenner Responds
text:
There are no plans for Caitlyn Jenner to dance with Donald Trump at the inauguration. (Photo by Frazer Harrison/Getty Images for GLAAD) 
Rumors surfaced that the president-elect was considering a two-step with the reality star in order to “mend fences” with the transgender community after a member of the incoming administration told Page Six it was in the works. 
Jenner’s representative said the rumors are not true. (RELATED: Caitlyn Jenner: ‘I Get More Flak For Being Conservative Than Being Transgender’) 
“This is a ridiculous story,” Jenner’s rep told People magazine. “There have been no discussions about who Caitlyn will or won’t dance with, or if she will dance at all. I can’t deal in hypotheticals and have no idea what any Trump aids hope happens.” (Photo: Alberto E. Rodriguez/Getty Images for GLAAD) 
“Of course, real question is if they danced, who would lead?”
